prompt: Write a poem about the sea.
pred:
by Sarah Kain Guthrie

The sea, oh the sea, vast and deep,
Eternal in its mysteries, a world to keep,
From shoreline to horizon, a canvas so grand,
Reflecting life’s beauty, with its every hand.

It gives and takes away, with its every wave,
Lashing against the shore, a living grave,
Yet its roar, a soothing melody to the ear,
Easing all our fears, and banishing all our fear.

It provides, and sustains, a bounteous feast,
From its abundant treasures, a world to seize,
From plankton to whales, a living chorus to sing,
Celebrating life’s beauty, with its every ring.

It connects us all, in its eternal flow,
From shore to shore, a world to know,
For though it’s vast, and deep, and wide,
The sea remembers us, and our hearts it will provide.

It remembers all, in its every wave,
From birth to death, a world to give,
And as we look into its living depths,
We are reminded, life’s beauty is in its every rush.

And so we come, to its shoreline once more,
